or upwelling regions. Sea surface temperature (SST) records from Moroccan sediment cores, extending back 2500 years, reveal anomalous and unprecedented cooling during the 20th century, which is consistent with increased upwelling. Upwelling-driven SSTs also vary out of phase with millennial-scale changes in Northern Hemisphere temperature anomalies (NHTAs) and show relatively warm conditions during the Little Ice Age and relatively cool conditions during the Medieval Warm Period. Together, these results suggest that coastal upwelling varies with NHTAs and that upwelling off northwest Africa may continue to intensify as global warming and atmospheric CO2 levels increase.",,"carbon dioxide; lead 210; sea water; surface water; carbon dioxide; global warming; Little Ice Age; Medieval Warm Period; nearshore environment; Northern Hemisphere; sea surface temperature; sediment core; temperature anomaly; twentieth century; upwelling; Africa; article; atmosphere; climate change; ecosystem; environmental impact; fishery; greenhouse effect; greenhouse gas; marine environment; oceanic regions; priority journal; sea surface temperature; sea surface waters; seashore; socioeconomics; Africa",,"carbon dioxide, 124-38-9, 58561-67-4; lead 210, 14255-04-0",,,,"Tomczak, M., Godfrey, J.S., (2003) Regional Oceanography: An Introduction, , www.es.flinders.edu.au/~mattom/regoc/pdfversion. html, Daya, Delhi, ed. 2; Pauly, D., Christensen, V., (1995) Nature, 374, p. 255; Bakun, A., (1990) Science, 247, p. 198; (2001) Climate Change 2001: Impacts, Adaptation, and Vulnerability, , Intergovernmental Panel on Climate Change, J. J. McCarthy, O. F. Canziani, N. A. Leary, D. J. Dokken, K. S. White, Eds, Cambridge Univ. Press, Cambridge; J. I. Goes, P. G. Thoppil, H. do R Gomes, J. T. Fasullo, Science 308, 545 (2005)Harley, C.D., (2006) Ecol. Lett, 9, p. 228; Anderson, D.M., Overpeck, J.T., Gupta, A.K., (2002) Science, 297, p. 596; Wooster, W.S., Bakun, A., McLain, D.R., (1976) J. Mar. Res, 34, p. 13